Here is the JavaScript code to generate and print out the ASCII character and hexade	codes for 0 to 7F:


```javascript
for (var i = 0; i <= 127; i++) {
    var ascii = String.fromCharCode(i);
    console.log('ASCII ' + i + ': ' + ascii + ' (0x' + i.toString(16).toUpperCase());
}
```

This code uses the `String.fromCharCode()` method to convert each number from 0 to 127 into its corresponding ASCII character, and then prints out the ASCII code along with its hexadecimal representation using `toString(16)` method to convert it into a two-digit uppercase hexadecimal string.


Note that this will only print out the first 128 characters of ASCII codes since 0 to 7F are within the ASCII range. If you want to include all ASCII characters, change `i <= 127` to `i < 256`.
